28{-# WARNING VEmpty   "Use 'D.empty' instead." #-}
29{-# WARNING VBool    "Use 'D.pBool' instead." #-}
30{-# WARNING VDec     "Use 'D.pDec' instead." #-}
31{-# WARNING VClock   "Use 'D.pClock' instead." #-}
32{-# WARNING VTime    "Use 'D.pTime' instead." #-}
33{-# WARNING VCode    "Use 'D.pCode' instead." #-}
34{-# WARNING VTerm    "Use 'D.pTerm' instead." #-}
35{-# WARNING VText    "Use 'D.pText' instead." #-}
36{-# WARNING VList    "Use 'D.pList' instead." #-}
37{-# WARNING VSet     "Use 'D.pSet' instead." #-}
38{-# WARNING VTie     "Use 'D.pTie' instead." #-}
39{-# WARNING VRel     "Use 'D.pRel' instead." #-}
40{-# WARNING VInterp  "Use 'D.pInterp' instead." #-}
41{-# WARNING VType    "Use 'D.pType' instead." #-}
42{-# WARNING VEnd     "Use 'D.end' instead." #-}
43
44-- | The Baala content type.
45data Content
46    = VEmpty                      -- ^ /Singleton:/   Sign of no ordinary type
47    | VBool    Bool               -- ^ /Numeric:/     Boolean type
48    | VDec     D.Decimal          -- ^ /Numeric:/     Decimal number type
49    | VClock   D.Clock            -- ^ /Numeric:/     Clock type
50    | VTime    D.Time             -- ^ /Numeric:/     Time type
51    | VCode    String             -- ^ /Textual:/     Code type
52    | VTerm    String             -- ^ /Textual:/     Term name type
53    | VText    String             -- ^ /Textual:/     Text type
54    | VList    [Content]           -- ^ /Collective:/  List type
55    | VSet     [Content]           -- ^ /Collective:/  Set type
56    | VTie     [B.Named Content]   -- ^ /Relational:/  Tie type (set of terms)
57    | VRel     (D.Rel Content)     -- ^ /Relational:/  Relation type
58    | VInterp  D.Interp           -- ^ /Relational:/  Interpretation type
59    | VType    D.Type             -- ^ /Meta:/        Type for type
60    | VEnd                        -- ^ /Singleton:/   The end of everything
61    deriving (Show)
62
63instance Eq Content where
64    x == y  = compare x y == EQ
65    x /= y  = compare x y /= EQ
66
67instance Ord Content where
68    -- simple
69    compare (VBool    x) (VBool    y)  = compare x y
70    compare (VDec     x) (VDec     y)  = compare x y
71    compare (VClock   x) (VClock   y)  = compare x y
72    compare (VTime    x) (VTime    y)  = compare x y
73    compare (VCode    x) (VCode    y)  = compare x y
74    compare (VTerm    x) (VTerm    y)  = compare x y
75    compare (VText    x) (VText    y)  = compare x y
76
77    -- complex
78    compare (VList    x) (VList    y)  = compare x y
79    compare (VSet     x) (VSet     y)  = compareAsSet x y
80    compare (VTie     x) (VTie     y)  = compareAsSet x y
81    compare (VRel     x) (VRel     y)  = compare x y
82    compare (VInterp  x) (VInterp  y)  = compare x y
83    compare (VType    x) (VType    y)  = compare x y
84
85    -- others
86    compare x y  = D.typeOrder x `compare` D.typeOrder y
87
88-- | Compare two lists as two sets.
89compareAsSet :: (Ord a) => [a] -> [a] -> Ordering
90compareAsSet x y = compare (Set.fromList x) (Set.fromList y)
91
92instance D.CTypeOf Content where
93    typeOf (VEmpty    )  = D.TypeEmpty
94    typeOf (VBool    _)  = D.TypeBool
95    typeOf (VDec     _)  = D.TypeDec
96    typeOf (VClock   c)  = D.TypeClock $ Just $ D.clockPrecision c
97    typeOf (VTime    t)  = D.TypeTime  $ Just $ D.timePrecision t
98    typeOf (VCode    _)  = D.TypeCode
99    typeOf (VTerm    _)  = D.TypeTerm
100    typeOf (VText    _)  = D.TypeText
101    typeOf (VList   cs)  = D.TypeList $ typeSum cs
102    typeOf (VSet    cs)  = D.TypeSet  $ typeSum cs
103    typeOf (VTie    cs)  = D.TypeTie  $ B.mapSndTo D.typeOf cs
104    typeOf (VRel     _)  = D.TypeRel []
105    typeOf (VInterp  _)  = D.TypeInterp
106    typeOf (VType    _)  = D.TypeType
107    typeOf (VEnd      )  = D.TypeEnd
108
109typeSum :: D.CTypeOf c => [c] -> D.Type
110typeSum cs = case B.unique $ map D.typeOf cs of
111               [t] -> t
112               ts  -> D.TypeSum ts
113
114instance D.CContent Content where
115    appendContent (VEmpty) x           = Right x
116    appendContent x (VEmpty)           = Right x
117    appendContent (VText x) (VText y)  = Right . VText $ x ++ y
118    appendContent x y                  = Msg.unmatchType (show (x, y))
119
120instance B.MixShortEncode Content where
121    mixShortEncode sh c =
122        case c of
123          VCode  s   -> B.mixString $ quote  (sh s) s
124          VText  s   -> B.mixString $ qquote (sh s) s
125          VTerm  s   -> B.mixString $ "'/" ++ s
126          VDec   n   -> B.mixString $ D.encodeDecimal n
127          VClock t   -> B.mixEncode t
128          VTime  t   -> B.mixEncode t
129          VBool  b   -> B.mixEncode b
130          VEmpty     -> B.mixString "()"
131          VEnd       -> B.mixString "(/)"
132
133          VList cs   -> D.mixBracketList $ mixBar cs
134          VSet  cs   -> D.mixBracketSet  $ mixBar cs
135          VTie  ts   -> B.mixBracketS S.tieOpen  S.tieClose  $ D.termsToMix1 sh ts
136          VRel  r    -> B.mixShortEncode sh r
137          VInterp i  -> B.mixEncode i
138          VType t    -> B.mixBracketS S.typeOpen S.typeClose $ B.mixEncode t
139        where
140          mixBar cs   = B.mixJoinBar $ map (B.mixShortEncode sh) cs
141
142quote :: Maybe String -> O.StringMap
143quote (Nothing) s   = "'" ++ s
144quote (Just s)  _   = s
145
146qquote :: Maybe String -> O.StringMap
147qquote (Nothing) "" = "\"\""
148qquote (Nothing) s  = S.angleQuote s
149qquote (Just s)  _  = s
150
151
152-- ----------------------  Simple
153
154instance D.CEmpty Content where
155    empty                    = VEmpty
156    isEmpty VEmpty           = True
157    isEmpty _                = False
158
159instance D.CEnd Content where
160    end                      = VEnd
161    isEnd VEnd               = True
162    isEnd _                  = False
163
164instance D.CBool Content where
165    pBool                    = VBool
166    gBool (VBool x)          = x
167    gBool _                  = B.bug "gBool"
168    isBool  (VBool _)        = True
169    isBool  _                = False
170
171instance D.CDec Content where
172    pDec                     = VDec
173    gDec (VDec x)            = x
174    gDec _                   = B.bug "gDec"
175    isDec  (VDec _)          = True
176    isDec  _                 = False
177
178instance D.CClock Content where
179    pClock                   = VClock
180    gClock  (VClock x)       = x
181    gClock  _                = B.bug "gClock"
182    isClock (VClock _)       = True
183    isClock _                = False
184
185instance D.CTime Content where
186    pTime                    = VTime
187    gTime  (VTime x)         = x
188    gTime  _                 = B.bug "gTime"
189    isTime (VTime _)         = True
190    isTime _                 = False
191
192instance D.CCode Content where
193    pCode                    = VCode
194    gCode (VCode s)          = s
195    gCode _                  = B.bug "gCode"
196    isCode  (VCode _)        = True
197    isCode  _                = False
198
199instance D.CTerm Content where
200    pTerm                    = VTerm
201    gTerm (VTerm s)          = s
202    gTerm _                  = B.bug "gTerm"
203    isTerm  (VTerm _)        = True
204    isTerm  _                = False
205
206instance D.CText Content where
207    pText                    = VText
208    gText (VText s)          = s
209    gText _                  = B.bug "gText"
210    isText  (VText _)        = True
211    isText  _                = False
212
213-- ----------------------  Complex
214
215instance D.CList Content where
216    pList                    = VList
217    gList (VList xs)         = xs
218    gList _                  = []
219    isList (VList _)         = True
220    isList _                 = False
221
222instance D.CSet Content where
223    pSet                     = VSet . B.omit D.isEmpty . B.unique
224    gSet (VSet x)            = x
225    gSet _                   = B.bug "gSet"
226    isSet  (VSet _)          = True
227    isSet  _                 = False
228
229instance D.CTie Content where
230    pTie                     = VTie 
231    gTie (VTie x)            = x
232    gTie _                   = B.bug "gTie"
233    isTie  (VTie _)          = True
234    isTie  _                 = False
235
236instance D.CRel Content where
237    pRel                     = VRel
238    gRel (VRel r)            = r
239    gRel _                   = B.bug "gRel"
240    isRel  (VRel _)          = True
241    isRel  _                 = False
242
243instance D.CInterp Content where
244    pInterp                  = VInterp
245    gInterp (VInterp r)      = r
246    gInterp _                = B.bug "gInterp"
247    isInterp  (VInterp _)    = True
248    isInterp  _              = False
249
250instance D.CType Content where
251    pType                    = VType
252    gType (VType r)          = r
253    gType _                  = B.bug "gType"
254    isType  (VType _)        = True
255    isType  _                = False

258-- ----------------------  Concrete type
259
260-- | @Judge@ for concrete baala content.
261type JudgeC = D.Judge Content
262
263-- | @Term@ for concrete baala content.
264type TermC = S.Term Content
265
266-- | @Rel@ for concrete baala content.
267type RelC = D.Rel Content
268
269-- | Shorthand function for the Baala content type.
270--
271--   >>> the $ D.pText "a"
272--   VText "a"
273--
274the :: Content -> Content
275{-# INLINE the #-}
276the = id
277
278-- | Decode the Baala content from string.
279--
280--   >>> stringC "'a"
281--   Right (VCode "a")
282--
283stringC :: String -> B.Ab Content
284stringC = D.stringContent
